    <p>Personal project from a crazy Catalan who hates gasoline but loves theater: a 90s American pickup turned into a full stealth EV with total combustion disguise. Looks like an old dirty V12 biturbo... but it's pure electric silently smoking supercars.</p>
    <p><span class="highlight">Creator:</span> A stoner from Sabadell with too much free time, a 3D printer, and a burning desire to troll the world.</p>
</div>

<div class="section">
    <h2>The Lore of El Fumado de Sabadell</h2>
    <p>Inspired by the BYD Shark ("that Chinese truck that looks like an F-150 but out-accelerates it"), taken to the extreme DIY level: "What if we make an old pickup look like a gas-guzzling muscle beast... but it's actually EV?".<br>Born on a beer night in Sabadell, with napkin sketches at the bar and memes about "fake engine bay".</p>
    <p>Goal: People go "damn, what a beast of a biturbo V12"... then lose their minds when they realize there's no real engine.</p>
</div>

